lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve's single largest intervention to prop up the U.S. economy, its $1.25 trillion program to buy mortgage-backed securities, came to a long-anticipated end on Wednesday, Sewell Chan reports in The New York Times.

headline.main: Fed Ends Its Purchasing of Mortgage Securities
